Diversity

Perl module for performing fast O(N) expected pairwise difference (epd) calculations. Input is a gapped alignment file in fasta format. Evaluation of probabilities is O(N) where N is the number of reads. Evaluation of diversity is O(1). Evaluation of error in the diversity is also O(1). 


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION


Eventually documentation will be organized as follows: After installing, will be able to find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Diversity

You will also be able to look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Diversity

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Diversity

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Diversity

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Diversity/


